text: unpopular opinion  suicidal people don t want to hear  it gets better  life isn t linear so if it gets better  by that logic it will also get worse at some point    some people  ahem  me  have been struggling with suicidal thoughts for years  for me it s been nine years  some stories i read on here are anywhere between a year and twenty years  so saying  it gets better  is really only half the story  sure  it might get better tomorrow but it might also take   years  it s harrowing to think i might have to live through that many years before i can fully manage my depressive thoughts and stop wanting to die  but false advertising doesn t make this any better  i wonder sometimes if the people saying it will get better have dealt with long depressive episodes and consistent suicidal thoughts themselves  a lot of people try to relate to depression by recalling a time in their life when they were sad  which is a valid experience and make senses if you re trying to empathize with something you don t entirely understand  but do you really think that the same advice that helped you through that minute  one off bout of depression is going to be suitable for people with sustained mental illness   i e    oh you have persistent depressive disorder  yeah i couldn t stop crying when my cat died either  take a walk to get your mind off it  it will pass  it s a complete mismatch    hearing arbitrary advice like this screams that your intent is not to understand but rather just feel like you ve helped the situation so you can sleep sound at night  checking the box  if you will  whose feelings have improved following your  it get s better  spiel  only yours  then you see the problem   i understand that not everyone knows the right thing to say but sometimes silence is better than nonsense   TLDR  with that being said  have any of my fellow  suicidal  folk received advice that actually worked for them or made them change their perspective  even a little  i would love to hear it
summary: Suicidal people don't want to hear it gets better. Some people have been struggling with depression for years, others for only a year or a year and some for up to 20 years. People who say it will get better don't have to deal with long depressive episodes and consistent suicidal thoughts.
cleaned: suicidal people not want hear get well people struggle depression year year year year people well not deal long depressive episode consistent suicidal thought
